Can you try execute and print python3 with the following command?

import pip; print(pip.pep425tags.get_supported())

Example:

$ python3
Python 3.5.1 (default, Dec 7 2015, 21:59:08)
[GCC 4.2.1 Compatible Apple LLVM 7.0.0 (clang-700.1.76)] on darwin
Type "help", "copyright", "credits" or "license" for more information.
import pip; print(pip.pep425tags.get_supported())
[('cp35', 'cp35m', 'macosx_10_10_x86_64'), ('cp35', 'cp35m', 'macosx_10_10_intel'), ('cp35', 'cp35m', 'macosx_10_10_fat64'), ('cp35', 'cp35m', 'macosx_10_10_fat32'),.....

> [GCC 4.2.1 Compatible Apple LLVM 7.0.0 (clang-700.1.76)] on darwin
> Type "help", "copyright", "credits" or "license" for more information.
> import pip; print(pip.pep425tags.get_supported())
